I guess it shouldn't allocate because `x` has enough capacity.
```julia
const x=Vector{Int}(undef, 1000)
empty!(x) 
@time prepend!(x, 10)
@time prepend!(x, 10)

0.000007 seconds (2 allocations: 16.844 KiB)
  0.000001 seconds
```

